'''Fabián Cornelio Balbuena González''' (born 23 August 1991) is a Paraguayan professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] for [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] club [[Grêmio FBPA|Grêmio]] and the [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay national team]].

He played for [[Club Cerro Porteño (Presidente Franco)|Cerro Porteño PF]], [[Club Rubio Ñu|Rubio Ñu]], [[Club Nacional|Nacional]] and [[Club Libertad|Libertad]] in the [[Paraguayan Primera División]], before joining [[Sport Club Corinthians Paulista|Corinthians]] of Brazil in 2016. He played 120 games for Corinthians, winning the [[Campeonato Paulista]] twice and the [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] once, and was named in the latter's 2017 [[Premio Craque do Brasileirao|team of the year]]. After three years with [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] in the [[Premier League]], he signed for Dynamo Moscow.

Balbuena made his senior international debut for Paraguay in 2015. He played for his national team at four [[Copa América]] tournaments, coming fourth in [[2015 Copa América|2015]].

==Club career==
===Paraguay===
Born in [[Ciudad del Este]], Balbuena was promoted to [[Club Cerro Porteño (Presidente Franco)|Cerro Porteño PF]]'s first team in 2010, after the arrival of new manager [[Eduardo Rivera (footballer)|Eduardo Rivera]]. He immediately became a starter under Rivera, playing in all the remaining seven matches of the campaign as his side achieved a mid-table position.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.com.br/noticia/713949_pai-queria-que-balbuena-estudasse-mas-ele-virou-jogador-capitao-aos-20-e-hoje-brilha-no-corinthians|title=Pai queria que Balbuena estudasse, mas ele virou jogador, capitão aos 20 e hoje brilha no Corinthians|trans-title=Balbuena's father wanted him to study, but he became a player, captain at 20 and today shines at Corinthians|publisher=[[ESPN Brasil]]|language=pt|date=28 July 2017|access-date=17 July 2018|archive-date=18 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180718001502/http://www.espn.com.br/noticia/713949_pai-queria-que-balbuena-estudasse-mas-ele-virou-jogador-capitao-aos-20-e-hoje-brilha-no-corinthians|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Balbuena became a regular starter in 2011, being also [[Captain (association football)|team captain]] as the club achieved promotion from [[Paraguayan División Intermedia|División intermedia]].{{citation needed|date=March 2022}}

Balbuena joined [[Club Rubio Ñu|Rubio Ñu]] ahead of the [[2013 Paraguayan Primera División season|2013 season]], but remained at the club for only six months before moving to defending champions [[Club Nacional]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.com.py/edicion-impresa/deportes/se-sumo-otro-mazacotte-592820.html|title=Se sumó otro Mazacotte|trans-title=Another Mazacotte joined|publisher=[[ABC Color]]|language=es|date=7 June 2013|access-date=17 July 2018}}</ref> At the latter side, he was also first-choice and reached the [[2014 Copa Libertadores Finals]], losing it to [[San Lorenzo de Almagro|San Lorenzo]].{{citation needed|date=March 2022}}

On 15 August 2014, [[Club Libertad|Libertad]] bought 50% of Balbuena's federative rights, and the player signed a four-year deal with the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.com.py/deportes/futbol/balbuena-ya-es-gumarelo-1276518.html|title=Balbuena ya es gumarelo|trans-title=Balbuena already is ''gumarelo''|publisher=ABC Color|language=es|date=15 August 2014|access-date=17 July 2018}}</ref> They won the [[2014 Paraguayan Primera División season|2014 Clausura]] tournament.{{citation needed|date=March 2022}}

===Corinthians===
On 16 February 2016, Balbuena moved abroad for the first time in his career after agreeing to a three-year deal with [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|Série A]] side [[Sport Club Corinthians Paulista|Corinthians]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.corinthians.com.br/balbuena-assina-com-corinthians-por-tres-temporadas/|title=Balbuena assina com Corinthians por três temporadas|trans-title=Balbuena signs with Corinthians for three seasons|publisher=SC Corinthians Paulista|language=pt|date=16 February 2016|access-date=17 July 2018}}</ref> He made his debut for the club nine days later by starting in a 1–1 [[Campeonato Paulista]] away draw against [[Esporte Clube São Bento|São Bento]], and scored his first goal on 19 March in a 4–0 home routing of [[Clube Atlético Linense|Linense]] for the same competition.{{citation needed|date=March 2022}}

A key defensive unit at ''Timão'', Balbuena lifted the [[2017 Campeonato Paulista]], [[2017 Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] and [[2018 Campeonato Paulista]] during his spell. On 24 April 2018, he signed a new four-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.corinthians.com.br/fabian-balbuena-renova-contrato-por-quatro-temporadas/|title=Fabián Balbuena renova contrato por quatro temporadas|trans-title=Fabián Balbuena renews contract for four seasons|publisher=SC Corinthians Paulista|language=pt|date=24 April 2018|access-date=17 July 2018}}</ref>

===West Ham United===
[[File:Hertha BSC vs. West Ham United 20190731 (092).jpg|left|thumb|Balbuena (furthest right) in a friendly against [[Hertha BSC]] in July 2019]]
On 14 July 2018, Balbuena signed for [[Premier League]] club [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] on a three-year deal, for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.whufc.com/news/articles/2018/july/14-july/west-ham-sign-paraguay-defender-balbuena|title=West Ham sign Paraguay defender Balbuena|publisher=West Ham United FC|date=14 July 2018|access-date=17 July 2018}}</ref> He made his debut on 12 August in a 4–0 defeat by [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45073328|title=Salah, Mane & Sturridge on target as Liverpool beat West Ham 4–0|date=12 August 2018|access-date=13 August 2018|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> On 27 October he scored his first goal for the Hammers to open the scoring at [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]], but deflected [[Wilfred Ndidi]]'s long-range shot into his own net for the equaliser; he was the first Paraguayan to score in England's top division since [[Antolín Alcaraz]] in May 2012.<ref>{{cite news |title=Leicester City 1&ndash;1 West Ham United |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45924072 |access-date=28 October 2018 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=27 October 2018}}</ref>

On 18 October 2020, Balbuena scored West Ham's first goal as they overturned a 3–0 deficit with eight minutes remaining to draw at London rivals [[Tottenham Hotspur]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hytner |first1=David |title=Lanzini's late gem completes stunning West Ham fightback at Tottenham |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/oct/18/tottenham-west-ham-premier-league-match-report |access-date=25 April 2021 |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=18 October 2020}}</ref> The following 24 April, he was sent off in a 1–0 home loss to another capital team, [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], for catching [[Ben Chilwell]] when making a clearance; the decision was criticised by manager [[David Moyes]] and various pundits.<ref>{{cite news |title=David Moyes: West Ham boss hits out at officials after Fabian Balbuena red card |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/56875602 |access-date=25 April 2021 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=24 April 2021}}</ref> The [[Red card (association football)|red card]] was overturned after West Ham appealed.<ref>{{cite news |title=Fabian Balbuena: West Ham defender's red card against Chelsea overturned on appeal |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/56907307 |access-date=27 April 2021 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=27 April 2021}}</ref> In May 2021, Balbuena was told by West Ham that his contract would not be renewed when it expired at the end of the [[2020–21 West Ham United F.C. season|2020–21 season]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.footballinsider247.com/sources-west-ham-tell-balbuena-to-find-new-club-as-moyes-transfer-plan-revealed/|title=West Ham news: Fabian Balbuena told to find new club|first=Wayne|last=Veysey|date=May 28, 2021}}</ref>

===Dynamo Moscow===
[[File:Paulistão A1 - São Bernardo 2x0 Corinthians 02.jpg|thumb|right|150px|Balbuena with [[Sport Club Corinthians Paulista|Corinthians]] in 2023]]

On 9 July 2021, he signed a four-year contract with [[Russian Premier League]] club [[FC Dynamo Moscow]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[FC Dynamo Moscow]]|url=https://fcdynamo.ru/news/fabian-balbuena-stal-igrokom-dinamo|title=Фабиан Бальбуэна стал игроком "Динамо"|date=9 July 2021|language=ru}}</ref>

On 10 July 2022, Balbuena suspended his contract with Dynamo Moscow for the 2022–23 season, having taken advantage of the [[FIFA]] ruling relating to the [[2022 Russian invasion of Ukraine|Russian invasion of Ukraine]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Fabián Balbuena suspends contract with Dynamo |url=https://en.fcdm.ru/news/fabian-balbuena-priostanovil-kontrakt-s-dynamo |website=en.fcdm.ru/ |publisher=FC Dynamo Moscow |access-date=10 July 2022 |date=10 July 2022}}</ref> Eight days later, he returned to [[Sport Club Corinthians Paulista|Corinthians]] for the period of his Dynamo contract suspension, until 30 June 2023.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Corinthians|url=https://www.corinthians.com.br/noticias/balbuena-e-o-novo-reforco-do-corinthians|title=Balbuena é o novo reforço do Corinthians|date=18 July 2022|access-date=18 July 2022|language=pt}}</ref>

At the end of this suspension, Balbuena returned to Dynamo in July 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sportrbc.ru/news/64a6e97c9a794711a13513b2|title=Парагвайский футболист Бальбуэна вернулся в "Динамо"|language=ru|date=2023-07-06|website=Sportrbc.ru}}</ref>
After returning to the Moscow club, Balbuena was chosen as the team captain for the next season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sportrbc.ru/news/64ba72be9a794764cf4362e1|title=Капитаном "Динамо" выбрали приостанавливавшего контракт легионера|language=ru|date=2023-07-21|website=Sportrbc.ru}}</ref>

Balbuena left Dynamo on 31 May 2025 as his contract expired.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Dynamo Moscow|url=https://fcdynamo.ru/news/fabian-balbuena-pokidaet-dynamo/|title=Фабиан Бальбуэна покидает "Динамо"|trans-title=Fabián Balbuena leaves Dynamo|date=31 May 2025|access-date=31 May 2025|language=ru}}</ref>

===Grêmio===
On 26 July 2025, Balbuena signed a contract with [[Grêmio FBPA|Grêmio]] in Brazil until 30 June 2027.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Grêmio|url=https://gremio.net/noticias/detalhes/29146/gremio|title=Grêmio anuncia a contratação do zagueiro Balbuena|trans-title=Grêmio announces the signing of defender Balbuena|date=26 July 2025|access-date=28 July 2025|language=pt}}</ref>

==International career==
First called up on 19 March 2015, Balbuena made his full international debut for [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay national team]] on 31 March by starting in a 1–0 [[Exhibition match|friendly]] loss against [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]] at the [[Arrowhead Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sbnation.com/soccer/2015/3/31/8323799/mexico-paraguay-2015-final-score-result|title=Mexico vs. Paraguay 2015: Final score 1–0, El Tri run rampant in Kansas City|publisher=[[SB Nation]]|date=31 March 2015|access-date=17 July 2018}}</ref> He was also named among the 23-man squads for the [[2015 Copa América]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.com.py/deportes/futbol/los-23-elegidos-1371359.html|title=Los 23 elegidos de Díaz|trans-title=Díaz's 23 chosen ones|publisher=ABC Color|language=es|date=28 May 2015|access-date=17 July 2018}}</ref> and the [[Copa América Centenario]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.com.py/edicion-impresa/deportes/solo-un-par-de-nuevos-entre-los-de-siempre-1478624.html|title=Solo un par de nuevos entre los de siempre|trans-title=Only a bunch of newbies among the usual ones|publisher=ABC Color|language=es|date=10 May 2016|access-date=17 July 2018}}</ref> He made his first competitive appearance at the latter in the final group game, a 1–0 loss to hosts the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] in which he was substituted at half time for attacker [[Juan Iturbe]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Shorthanded USA outlasts Paraguay 1&ndash;0 to advance to 2016 Copa America quarterfinals |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2016/06/12/01/48/160611-mnt-shorthanded-defeats-paraguay-1-0-to-adavnce-to-copa-america-quarterfinals |access-date=28 October 2018 |publisher=U.S. Soccer |date=11 June 2016}}</ref>

At the [[2019 Copa América]] in Brazil, Paraguay faced the [[Brazil national football team|host team]] in the quarter-finals, and Balbuena was sent off after an hour for fouling [[Roberto Firmino]] when the Brazilian was clear on goal; the game ended goalless and Brazil won on penalties.<ref>{{cite news |title=Copa America: Brazil beat Paraguay on penalties to reach semi-finals |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48775057 |access-date=28 July 2024 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=28 June 2019}}</ref>

On 23 September 2022, Balbuena scored his first international goal, a late header that was the only goal of a friendly win over the [[United Arab Emirates national football team|United Arab Emirates]] in [[Wiener Neustadt]], Austria.<ref>{{cite news |title=Paraguay, con gol de Balbuena, superó a los Emiratos Arabes|trans-title=Paraguay, with goal by Balbuena, overcame the United Arab Emirates |url=https://fdpradio.com/paraguay-con-gol-de-balbuena-supero-a-los-emiratos-arabes/ |access-date=28 July 2024 |publisher=FDP Radio |date=23 September 2022 |language=Spanish}}</ref> In a 1–0 friendly loss away to [[Peru national football team|Peru]] on 16 November, Balbuena and opponent [[Alexander Succar]] were sent off for fighting.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gresca entre ambos: Alexander Succar y Fabián Balbuena fueron expulsados en amistoso entre Perú y Paraguay|trans-title=Fracas between the two: Alexander Succar and Fabián Balbuena were sent off in friendly between Peru and Paraguay|url=https://rpp.pe/futbol/seleccion-peruana/peru-vs-paraguay-alexander-succar-y-fabian-balbuena-fueron-expulsados-en-amistoso-noticia-1447318 |access-date=28 July 2024 |publisher=RPP |date=16 November 2022 |language=Spanish}}</ref>

